Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Jupyter notebook won't start

Check if port 8888 is already in use: netstat -tuln | grep 8888
Try alternative port: jupyter notebook --port=8889
Ensure you're in the correct directory
Issue: Pandas cannot find CSV file

Verify file path is correct relative to notebook location
Use os.getcwd() to check current directory
Use absolute paths if relative paths fail
Issue: Plots not displaying in Jupyter

Add %matplotlib inline at the top of notebook
Ensure plt.show() is called after plot creation
Check if matplotlib backend is configured correctly
Issue: Memory errors with large datasets

Load data in chunks using pd.read_csv(chunksize=1000)
Use dtype parameter to optimize memory usage
Filter unnecessary columns early in processing
